videos.description: Kentucky's PJ Washington comes up with a massive rim defense. Then Quade Green speeds down the floor for a fast-break lay-in.
videos.headline: Washington's swat sets up fast-break bucket

videos.description: PJ Washington gives Kentucky the lead with under 30 seconds to go in the first half after he steals a pass and drives for a layup.
videos.headline: Washington finishes fast-break and-1 in final seconds of 1st half

videos.description: Arkansas' Daryl Macon crosses up a Kentucky defender, then drains a 3-pointer moments before the first-half buzzer sounds.
videos.headline: Macon puts defender on skates, sinks 3 before the buzzer

videos.description: Kentucky head coach John Calipari didn't think his team was going to score after watching the start of the game, but glad his Wildcats battled back.
videos.headline: Calipari: 'This is a challenge, this is a good team we're playing'

videos.description: Daniel Gafford creates space in the paint then smashes down a two-handed flush.
videos.headline: Gafford punishes the rim

videos.description: Daniel Gafford swats away two Kentucky shots in a matter of seconds to get the crowd rocking.
videos.headline: Gafford has no regard for Kentucky's layups

videos.description: Arkansas' Anton Beard feeds an outlet pass to Daryl Macon for a layup then drills a pull-up 3 on the next fast break.
videos.headline: Beard owns the fast break against Kentucky

videos.description: Kentucky's Kevin Knox breaks down how the Wildcats were able to turn their slow start into a win at Arkansas.
videos.headline: Knox: 'We came in here and did what we had to do'

videos.description: The Wildcats shoot 46 percent from the floor and outrebound the Razorbacks 46-29 in the win.
videos.headline: Kentucky defeats Arkansas 87-72

videos.description: Kevin Knox leads the Wildcats with 23 points and overcomes a deficit in the second half to cruise to an 87-72 win on the road against the Razorbacks.
videos.headline: Kentucky rolls in second half, tops Arkansas
